#25: 
Subject: [patch 15/28] drivers/input/touchscreen: convert to dynamic input_dev allocation

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*gunze)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct gunze)...)
#108: FILE: drivers/input/touchscreen/gunze.c:123:
+	gunze = kzalloc(sizeof(struct gunze), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

ERROR:ASSIGN_IN_IF: do not use assignment in if condition
#263: FILE: drivers/input/touchscreen/mk712.c:176:
+	if (!(mk712_dev = input_allocate_device())) {

Do not use assignments in if condition.
Example::

  if ((foo = bar(...)) < BAZ) {

should be written as::

  foo = bar(...);
  if (foo < BAZ) {

